<%= form_for @post do |f| %>
  <div>
    <%= f.label :title %>
    <%= f.text_field :title %>
  </div>

  <div>
    <%= f.label :content %>
    <%= f.text_area :content %>
  </div>

  <div>
    <%= f.label :categories %>
    <%= f.collection_check_boxes :category_ids, @categories, :id, :name %>
  </div>

  <div>
    <%= f.fields_for :categories do |categories_attributes| %>
      <%= categories_attributes.text_field :name %>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <%= f.submit %>
<% end %>


<!-- The form should include check boxes for us to select categories as well as a text field to create a new category. You should do this with a nested form so that our controller stays thin. Also, typing in a Category name that already exists should not create a new category. Instead, if we type in a category that already exists, we should select it from the database and associate the post we've created with the existing category -->